2010-04-28 09:53  alpha@paranoici.org

	* trunk/ardesia/src/annotate.c, 
          trunk/ardesia/src/main.c: 
          - Review of the z-stack window Z-order I see that the set_keep_above
            has different behaviour unde linux and win7 and then I have decided
	    to avoid to use it Now the Z order is fixed with the
	    gtk_window_set_transient_for function I describe the window
	    fixed zeta order starting from below: - the background window -
	    the bar window - the annotation window - the transient dialogs
	    and the transient text window The annotation window when the
	    pointer leave the pointer does: - present the bar (to avoid to
	    have the annotation window without the bar window that is its
	    controller) - grab the pointer - put the pen, eraser or text
	    icon cursor as pointer icon depending on the selected option
	    throught the ardesia bar The annotation window when the pointer
	    is moved upon the window bar does: - restore the normal cursor
	    for the pointer - ungrab the pointer - present the bar (to avoid
	    to remain without controller) I have not tested this on win7 but
	    I hope that this will work


