2010-03-08 16:06  alpha@paranoici.org

	* trunk/ardesia/src/annotate.c, 
          trunk/ardesia/src/annotate.h,
	  trunk/ardesia/src/callbacks.c,
          trunk/ardesia/src/text_widget.c:
	  - The window for the text insertion now does not use masking
	    shaping.
            I use now a toplevel maximized window instead of a
	    fullscreen window This mean that now after you have chose the
	    text focus you can use only the gnome menu bar.
            The cursor is not active below the transparent window on the desktop;
            I have done this because there is not assurance about who grabs the focus
	    Now you can use the normal keyboard or select your preferred
	    application to send keyboard event to the text window 
            I have successfully tested the ardesia text insertion with cellwriter
	    and with the onboard virual keybord successfully 
            I have seen that ardesia does not work very well with xvkbd because this
	    virtual keyboard even with the "always on top" option loose the
	    focus, and then you must retake it all the times In any case if
	    you want try with an other program see if there is a keep above
	    option or some of equivalent


